Request More Information     Apply to Wagner                                                 Application Review   Admissions at NYU is conducted on a deadline-driven timetable.  Once an application is submitted, it will be reviewed for completeness and forwarded to the Admissions Committee for review. We review all applications as is, however applications that are missing materials are at a profound disadvantage. The Admissions Committee begins reviewing fall applications in December of the prior year. Spring application review begins in September of the prior fall. Master's applicants receive a decision by e-mail according to the Notification Timetable. NYU Wagner will continue to accept applications after the deadline on a space available basis.   Merit-Based Scholarship Consideration   Applicants seeking a merit-based scholarship should complete the application process as early as possible. As long as all required materials are received, then the applicant will be considered for all available merit-based scholarships.   Click here to request more information about programs at NYU Wagner.   Applying Online   We offer a Web-based application to make our application process as easy and convenient as possible. We do not accept paper applications. The non-refundable application fee is $85 for Spring 2014 and Fall 2014 entry terms.   PPIA, Teach for America, AmeriCorps and PeaceCorps participants are eligible for an application fee waiver. Proof of participation must be submitted according to the fee waiver policies and instructions outlined on the online application. The application fee can also be waived for individuals who demonstrate need at NYU Wagner’s discretion. Follow the instructions in the application to seek an application fee waiver.                                                                                © NYU Wagner   295 Lafayette Street, New York, NY 10012-9604   212.998.7400   Copyright and Fair Use   Contact Us   Sitemap   New York University

Request More Information     Apply to Wagner                                                 Application Review   Admissions at NYU is conducted on a deadline-driven timetable.  Once an application is submitted, it will be reviewed for completeness and forwarded to the Admissions Committee for review. We review all applications as is, however applications that are missing materials are at a profound disadvantage. The Admissions Committee begins reviewing fall applications in December of the prior year. Spring application review begins in September of the prior fall. Master's applicants receive a decision by e-mail according to the Notification Timetable. NYU Wagner will continue to accept applications after the deadline on a space available basis.   Merit-Based Scholarship Consideration   Applicants seeking a merit-based scholarship should complete the application process as early as possible. As long as all required materials are received, then the applicant will be considered for all available merit-based scholarships.   Click here to request more information about programs at NYU Wagner.   Applying Online   We offer a Web-based application to make our application process as easy and convenient as possible. We do not accept paper applications. The non-refundable application fee is $85 for Spring 2014 and Fall 2014 entry terms.   PPIA, Teach for America, AmeriCorps and PeaceCorps participants are eligible for an application fee waiver. Proof of participation must be submitted according to the fee waiver policies and instructions outlined on the online application. The application fee can also be waived for individuals who demonstrate need at NYU Wagner’s discretion. It is not a single event or activity, but rather a process that anticipates and analyzes potential impacts of a project from the user’s perspective. Business Change Management guides and informs project activities and planning to help manage users’ expectations, resistance and buy-in. Studies have shown that projects are more likely to succeed with a clearly defined change management team and approach.   Visit the PSO Toolkit page to learn more about the key tools and templates used for Project Management, Business Change Management and Business Process Improvement.        Business Change Management Overview        The PSO’s Change Management Team provides readiness assessments, communications, training, post-implementation support planning and stakeholder/sponsorship activities from a project’s inception through post-deployment.        ADKAR Model        Using the ADKAR model, a methodology created by Prosci Research , the PSO Business Change Management team will manage and monitor fundamental elements of a change caused by a new system or project. This includes viewing all phases of a project through the user’s lens while keeping in mind NYU’s various school and organizational needs and differences, ensuring that users are “ready, willing and able” to adopt the change. See the diagram below for more information about the ADKAR Model.   The ADKAR Model (Awareness, Desire, Knowledge, Ability, Reinforcement) helps project teams understand the change position of both individuals and groups impacted by a project.
